Could we merge this logic into the `ipv4` method and have non-private address classes? I'm thinking something like:

```python
def ipv4(self, network=False, private=None, address_class=None):
    if private is None and address_class is None:
        # pretty much the old logic
    if private is True:
        classes = {
            'a': (167772160, 184549375, 24),
            'b': (2886729728, 2887778303, 20),
            'c': (3232235520, 3232301055, 16),
        }
  if private is False:
        classes = {
            'b': (2886729728, 2887778303, 16),
            'c': (3232235520, 3232301055, 8),
        }
```

should be:
data['WriteRequest'] = {}
data['WriteRequest']['Token'] = token

We could save a line with spread:

    const groups = $rootScope.repos.reduce((acc, repo, i, a, group = v => v.repository_group.name) => (
      { ...acc, [group(repo)]: [...acc[group(repo)] || [], repo] }
    ), {});

And slightly less terse names will make it easier to interpret, I think.  Would you mind doing them all like this?

It looks like this `has_method()` predicate also has the side-effect of actually calling the method. That can have strange side-effects in user code and it's a bit wasteful.

How about reworking this to check whether the attribute is callable. You'll need to adjust the tests, but maybe something like:

    def has_callable(obj, name):
        return callable(getattr(obj, name))

...and then use `has_callable()` instead of `has_method()`.  When the attribute doesn't exist we'll get `None` from `getattr()` and `callable()` will return `False`.

@ankurankan IMO we need not perform this check(earlier this check was in get_cardinality method) in this method at all .
The following check of check_model will be sufficient 
```
if not all(isinstance(factor_node, DiscreteFactor) for factor_node in factor_nodes):
            raise ValueError('Factors not associated for all the random variables')  
```

This can be refactored using an `else` clause on the loop:

```python

# Only skip a column if there is no overridden column
# which does not have a Foreign Key.
for column in prop.columns:
    if not column.foreign_keys:
        break
else:
    continue
```

> Btw, the gateway (and other Xiaomi devices / devices accessible with the Mi Home app, like Yeelight bulbs) are also discoverable over mDNS with _miio._udp).

D'oh! Fairly speaking, I wanted to play with mDNS regarding that, but that slipped, partly because I'm not much familiar with mDNS, and would need to dig into it. So instead I just used info from https://github.com/louisZL/lumi-gateway-local-api/blob/master/device_discover.md#1-网关设备发现设备发现不加密 .

@rytilahti , would you submit an alternative PR, using mDNS? If not, I can look into it, but per above, it would take me some time to dig into it. But we surely better use existing generic discovery protocols rather than add support for adhoc vendor-specific ones.

